  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The administration of agar jelly may increase the number of defecation and the volume of
      feces, and then may improve fecal condition in chronic constipated patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Each subject eats one cap of agar jelly shortly before having dinner every day for 4 weeks.

      At 0, 7th, 14th, 21th, and 28th day , the frequency of defecation and defecation condition is
      assessed.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
